The best model that simultaneously delivers industry-standard accuracy, production line speed, and runs perfectly without a costly GPU is EfficientAD.
1. Why it meets Industry Standard AccuracyOn the industry benchmark MVTec AD dataset, EfficientAD achieves an outstanding 99.1% to 99.5% Image AUROC score, making it functionally identical in accuracy to PatchCore. However, unlike typical anomaly detection networks that get confused by complex scenes, EfficientAD incorporates a uniquely structured Patch Description Network (PDN). 
This network uses strict receptive fields ensuring that fine-grained local pixels map directly to accurate defect regions, allowing it to easily spot micro-defects or larger "logical" structure anomalies (like a missing component)


1. Industry-standard accuracy

Yes. On the MVTec AD benchmark, EfficientAD achieves very high AUROC scores (around 99%+), making it competitive with leading anomaly detection methods like PatchCore and FastFlow on that dataset.

However:

MVTec AD contains 15 product categories.
Textile in MVTec is relatively controlled.
Real textile production lines usually have:
Different fabric colors
Different textures
Variable lighting
Fabric movement
Motion blur
Different weave patterns

So 99% on MVTec does not automatically mean 99% in a factory.
